General Instructions:
	- Please follow the instructions stated in the INSTALL file for detailed instructions on how to install (downloading .tar files, unpack/extract using gtar) and run the program.
	- To run the program navigate to the "bin/" directory and run the main executatables on different servers/accounts.
	- In order to start the server to be connected to a port and the client connected to the server's port.
	Ex:
		- Step #1: Run "./pokerserver 10080" on the server crystalcove
		- Step #2: Run "./pokerclient crystalcove 10080" on a different server"
	- After executing ./pokerclient use the ASCII interface to send messages to the server.

Alpha Version Notes:
	- In the latest version the client is able to send messages to the server.
	- Once the client is shut down through 'bye' or 'shutdown' the lastest client side GUI will open.
	- The client side GUI is able to take input from the user and save the username and password in memory.

Currently Working On:
	- The GUI for the poker game on the client side as well as the server side GUI.
	- More work on the poker game logic.
	- Working to integrate the GUI with the client and server connection.
	- Poker bot to fill in seats

